title: Weekly Review With Clay and Buck H2 - Nov 5 2022
itunes:title: Weekly Review With Clay and Buck H2 - Nov 5 2022
description:
Clay goes over what the polls and the political betting markets he loves to watch are saying. Stacey Abrams and Beto O'Rourke have spent a combined $150M, neither has ever led in a single poll this election cycle. Joy Behar is sick of Republicans complaining about crime. Hochul says she's the underdog in New York. Senator Tom Cotton joins Clay and Buck to discuss the midterms and his new book: Only the Strong. Democrats are throwing good money after bad in this election. C&B and martial arts movies.

Follow Clay & Buck on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/c/clayandbuck
